sentences.sentence: At the first cast I hooked a huge fish, probably a tench.
sentences.translation: 第一次抛竿我就钓到了一条大鱼，可能是条丁鲷。

sentences.sentence: Tench wrote that the judge had e-mailed him to confirm he had guessed the secret code right.
sentences.translation: 坦奇在文章中写道，法官给他发了封电子邮件，证实他破译出的答案是正确的。

sentences.sentence: When Danny Lamont Jones showed up at Tench Tilghman Middle School in East Baltimore, he was living only a few blocks away in a homeless shelter.
sentences.translation: 丹尼·拉蒙特·琼斯刚上巴尔的摩东区的坦奇蒂尔曼中学时，就住在离学校几个街区远的一个无家可归者的庇护所。
